HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 493
By Clemmons
A RESOLUTION to honor the memory of Denis Michael Gilmore,
MD FACS, of Nashville.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly were greatly saddened to learn of
the passing of Dr. Denis Michael Gilmore of Nashville; and
WHEREAS, an extraordinary physician who was beloved by his patients and their
families, Dr. Denis Gilmore was widely respected by his colleagues and was a consummate
professional who worked assiduously to improve the quality of life for his fellow citizens in
numerous capacities; and
WHEREAS, born on July 28, 1980, in Belleville, New Jersey, Dr. Denis Gilmore grew up
in Kearny, New Jersey, and graduated from Vanderbilt University in 2002; and
WHEREAS, pursuing a career in medicine, Dr. Gilmore graduated from The Royal
College of Surgeons in Dublin, Ireland, in 2007; completed his residency at Beth Israel
Deaconess Medical Center in Boston, Massachusetts, in 2015; and did his fellowship at
Vanderbilt University Medical Center through 2018; and
WHEREAS, a thoracic surgeon employed by Centennial Medical Center, Dr. Denis
Gilmore served as the Division Chief of Thoracic Surgery, Chair of the Professional Practice
Evaluation Committee, and Chair of the Robotics Committee; he was an esteemed member of
ABTS, ACS, STS, and STSA; and
WHEREAS, a devoted husband and father, Dr. Gilmore enjoyed the loving
companionship of his wife, Erin MacConchie Gilmore, and was the proud father of two sons,
Nate and Jake; and
WHEREAS, Dr. Gilmore always made his family his top priority, ensuring that he was
there for his boys and his wife, particularly at school events and hockey and baseball games,
and he helped coach his sons' Little League teams at McCabe Park; and
